{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nNon-structural findings (coherence and other plan-semantics criteria) re-litigate closed children\ntoo, and carry no `_container_child`. Without a finding<->closed-child association we cannot tell a\nlive signal from noise, and cannot distinguish plan-semantics from delivered-functionality.\n\n## What\n\nAdd a SEPARATE Pass-2 sub-call `plan_review_completion` in `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py`,\nmirroring the `plan_review_novelty` sub-call (its own contract + prompt), that ALONE receives the\ndelivered-children manifest (their own AC text) and emits, per finding, three atomic sub-answers:\nATTRIBUTION (closed child id or none; structural pass-through for G3/G4 `_container_child`),\nCONTAINMENT (`limited-to-closed | spans-open-or-system | n/a`), LAYER\n(`plan-semantics | delivered-functionality | n/a`). Write the rubric prompt at\n`src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_completion.md`, register the contract, and add it to the\nderived prompt index. Bounded/validated outputs; every ambiguous value fails toward keep. Frozen\nwording (not regenerated per run) per G-Eval guidance.\n\n## Scope\n\n- IN: the sub-call + contract registration + the prompt + output parsing/validation + prompt-index\n  entry.\n- OUT: the Pass-3 drop decision (separate story); the gold-set calibration (separate story).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A `plan_review_completion` sub-call exists, registered like `plan_review_novelty`, receiving ONLY the delivered-children manifest (Pass-1 independence preserved).\n- [ ] Per finding it emits {attribution, containment, layer} with the closed enums above; malformed/insufficient answers coerce to the keep-safe value.\n- [ ] G3/G4 attribution is taken structurally from `_container_child` (not re-asked); a None/unattributed finding is never force-attributed.\n- [ ] The rubric prompt `plan_review_completion.md` exists, is in the prompt index, and passes the CI drift gate; wording is frozen.\n- [ ] Unit tests cover parsing + the fail-safe coercions for each sub-answer.\n\n## Sub-call contract (fully specified)\n\nClosed enums (each a closed set; fail-safe value in brackets):\n- `attribution`: `<closed-child-ticket-id>` | `none` [none]. `none` = not about any closed child\n  (open child, the container itself, or cross-cutting). For G3/G4 findings the value is taken\n  STRUCTURALLY from `_container_child` (deterministic, not LLM-asked); for all other criteria it is\n  LLM-emitted and VALIDATED against the delivered-children id set (an id not in the set -> none).\n- `containment`: `limited-to-closed` | `spans-open-or-system` | `n-a` [spans-open-or-system].\n- `layer`: `plan-semantics` | `delivered-functionality` | `n-a` [delivered-functionality].\nOnly `containment=limited-to-closed` + `layer=plan-semantics` + a delivered-now attribution can\nenable a drop; every other value keeps.\n\nOutput contract: a `CompletionSubAnswers` model {attribution:str, containment:Literal[...],\nlayer:Literal[...]} per finding, registered as the `plan_review_completion` contract via\n`register_contracts()` (mirroring `novelty_model` -> `plan_review_novelty`, passes.py:147), prompt\n`src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_completion.md`.\n\nDeterminism: Pass-3 is deterministic GIVEN the sub-answers — attribution is deterministic for\ncontainer-coverage findings (`_container_child`) and LLM-emitted+validated otherwise, exactly as\nPass-2 severity is LLM-emitted while Pass-3 decide is deterministic.\n\nManifest assembly (OWNER: this story, in `orchestrator.py`): iterate the epic's children, call\n`delivered_now` per child, collect each delivered child's own AC text into the delivered-children\nmanifest handed to the sub-call (the sub-call ALONE receives it, mirroring novelty's prior-findings).\n\nDegrade path: total sub-call failure (LLM error / parse failure / timeout) -> emit NO completion\nsub-answers -> the completion floor drops NOTHING that run (all kept), mirroring `novelty()`==0.0\n(carryover, never dropped). Fail toward keep.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria (contract hardening)\n\n- [ ] Each of `attribution` / `containment` / `layer` is a CLOSED enum exactly as listed above; the parser coerces any unknown/missing value to the bracketed fail-safe (which keeps).\n- [ ] `containment=limited-to-closed` is the exact value the Pass-3 floor checks (no `limited` vs `limited-to-closed` drift across stories).\n- [ ] The `plan_review_completion` contract + `CompletionSubAnswers` model + prompt file exist and are registered like `plan_review_novelty`; a test asserts registration.\n- [ ] The delivered-children manifest assembler (in `orchestrator.py`) is implemented and unit-tested; the sub-call receives ONLY that manifest (Pass-1 independence).\n- [ ] Total sub-call failure degrades to zero drops (floor inert that run), with a test."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782975256254737001,"uuid":"72763910-629a-44d9-984e-a87e4a880ca0"}